4.28.20  1:21 pm   So I'm a sophomore who's been in choir for a few years now. I haven't been having any real issues with singing for academic reasons, but I'm having trouble transitioning my singing voice to more casual, hobby-related stuff. The problem is, school has only taught me to sing like a member of a choir, when that's really one out of a billion different styles one could be singing.

So I'm having trouble transitioning my choir voice into my more pop-related voice.

     It's become really hard to judge when I'm actually singing well, or when I sound absolutely terrible, just because I'm not used to judging this style of singing.

     Basically, how do you know when you've nailed down the vocals and got a great voice? Because I know you do!
